cheap by western standards; at rp 15,000 and up a small bottle costs the same as a full meal in a local eatery. in tourist centres, happy hours are widely publicised before and after sunset, with regular (stubbie) bottles of beer going for rp 10,000 to 20,000 and the large bottles for rp 18,000 to 30,000. bali produces its own wines, with hatten [58] being the oldest and most popular brand, available in white, red, rose (most popular) and sparkling varieties. quality is inconsistent, but the rose is usually ok and much cheaper than imported wines, which can easily top 